{"title_page": "List of awards and nominations received by Little Mix", "text_new": "{{Use British English|date=June 2017}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2017}}\n \n* <!--    Please, only add Notable awards with reliable sources, avoid magazines polls. --->  \n{{Infobox musician awards|name=Little Mix|image=Little Mix 11 (25844324432).jpg|caption=|collapse=yes|wins=42|nominations=99\n<!-- Total of all nominations either won, nominated or still pending -->\n<!-- Only ceremonies that are highly anticipated or well-known in the public. -->\n|award1=[[BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards]]|award1W=4|award1N=9\n|award2=[[Billboard Women in Music|''Billboard'' Latin Music Awards]]|award2W=0|award2N=1\n|award3=BIMA Awards|award3N=1|award3W=1\n|award4=[[Bravo Otto]]|award4W=2|award4N=3\n|award5=[[BRIT Awards]]|award5W=2|award5N=9\n|award6=[[Glamour Awards]]|award6W=3|award6N=4\n|award7=[[Global Awards]]|award7W=5|award7N=9\n|award8=[[iHeartRadio Music Awards]]|award8W=1|award8N=4\n|award9=[[Japan Gold Disc Award]]|award9W=2|award9N=2\n|award10=[[MTV Europe Music Awards]]|award10W=4|award10N=8\n|award11=[[Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]]|award11W=1|award11N=1\n|award12=[[Meus Pr\u00eamios Nick]]|award12W=1|award12N=1\n|award13=[[Popjustice \u00a320 Music Prize]]|award13W=3|award13N=6\n|award14=[[Radio Disney Music Awards]]|award14W=1|award14N=2\n|award15=[[Shorty Awards]]|award15W=0|award15N=3\n|award16=[[Silver Clef Award]]|award16W=1|award16N=1\n|award17=[[Teen Choice Awards]]|award17W=2|award17N=12\n}}\n\n[[Little Mix]] is a British four-piece [[girl group]] formed in 2011, consisting of members Perrie Edwards, Jade Thirlwall, Leigh-Anne Pinnock and Jesy Nelson.<ref name=\"ITV Profile 2011\">{{cite web|work=[[ITV (TV network)|ITV]]|title=Little Mix|year=2011|url=http://xfactor.itv.com/2011/finalists/little-mix|series=[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]|accessdate=21 December 2011}}</ref> They were formed exclusively for the [[The X Factor (UK series 8)|eighth series]] of ''[[The X Factor (UK)|The X Factor]]'' in 2011 and became the first group to win the competition. Following their victory, they signed with  [[Syco Music|Syco Records]] and released a cover of [[Damien Rice]]'s \"[[Cannonball (Damien Rice song)|Cannonball]]\" as their winner's single.\n\nThroughout their career Little Mix have received numerous accolades during their career including two Brit Awards, four MTV Europe Music Awards, four BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards, three Glamour Awards, five Global Music Awards, two Japanese Gold Disc Awards, two Teen Choice Awards, one Radio Disney Music Award, one iHeartRadio Music Award, and one O2 Silver Clef award.\n\n==Attitude Awards==\nThe '''Attitude Awards''' is hosted by British magazine [[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] to honor the LGBT+ community and its allies.<ref>{{cite web |title=ATTITUDE-AWARDS |url=https://attitude.co.uk/tag/attitude-awards/ |website=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] |accessdate=30 October 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=WATCH THE WINNERS OF THE ATTITUDE AWARDS COLLECT THEIR PRIZES |url=https://attitude.co.uk/article/watch-the-winners-of-the-attitude-awards-collect-their-prizes/19366/ |website=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] |accessdate=30 October 2019 |date=12 October 2018}}</ref>\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Honorary Gay Award\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=ATTITUDE'S HONORARY GAY AWARD: LITTLE MIX |url=https://attitude.co.uk/article/attitudes-honorary-gay-award-little-mix-1/19322/ |website=[[Attitude (magazine)|Attitude]] |accessdate=30 October 2019 |date=11 October 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Akingbade |first1=Tobi |title=Little Mix, Scarlett Moffatt, Ellie Goulding and Pixie Lott bring the fire for Attitude Awards 2018 |url=https://metro.co.uk/2018/10/12/little-mix-scarlett-moffatt-ellie-goulding-and-pixie-lott-bring-the-fire-for-attitude-awards-2018-8031554/ |website=[[Metro (British newspaper)|Metro]] |accessdate=30 October 2019 |date=12 October 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards==\nThe [[BBC Radio 1|BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards]] is an award show by the British radio station [[BBC Radio 1]] to honor the top artists in music and acting of the year. Little Mix have received four awards from nine nominations.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2013\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Best British Group\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/profiles/S8BP9HytvP5sBDtdKZX57S/teen-awards-winners-2013|title=Teen Awards Winners 2013|work=BBC|accessdate=2015-05-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"| 2015\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"a\">{{cite web|url=http://www.sugarscape.com/music/news/a1083599/radio-1-teen-awards-2015-nominations/|title=FULL BBC RADIO 1 TEEN AWARDS 2015 NOMINATIONS: LITTLE MIX, ONE DIRECTION, ED SHEERAN AND MORE|publisher=Sugarscape|accessdate=2015-10-29}}</ref>\n|-\n| Embrace Your Uniqueness\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p037hq66|title=Little Mix alternative Teen Award|work=BBC|accessdate=2015-11-09}}</ref>\n|-\n| \"[[Black Magic (song)|Black Magic]]\"\n| Best British Single\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"a\" />\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Best British Group\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/nm62NrB7rG6Hrb9SflnZkW/best-british-group</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| 2017\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>http://www.mtv.co.uk/little-mix/news/dua-lipa-little-mix-ariana-grande-and-more-win-big-at-the-radio-1-teen-awards</ref>\n|-\n| Jade Thirlwall <small>(Little Mix)</small>\n| Most Entertaining Celeb\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/2mN7kcB5dFhHwffQJ3qPVX1/most-entertaining-celeb</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best British Group\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards - Best British Group |url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/1KSYHxWL53vdqnHkHQJsYTT/best-british-group |website=BBC |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20180810141901/http://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/1KSYHxWL53vdqnHkHQJsYTT/best-british-group |archivedate=August 10, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2019\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Group\n| {{win}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=BBC Radio 1 Teen Awards - Best Group|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/articles/1mXByz4sYpDTw9Z1Rf9BnVN/best-group|website=BBC|accessdate=October 15, 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Billboard Latin Music Awards==\nThe [[Billboard Latin Music Awards]] grew out of the Billboard Music Awards program from Billboard Magazine, an industry publication charting the sales and radio airplay success of musical recordings.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Crossover Artist of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/amp/articles/columns/latin/8098517/2018-billboard-latin-music-awards-nominations|title=Billboard Latin Music Awardsc2018|work=Billboard|accessdate=2018-02-09}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Bravo Otto==\nEstablished in 1957, the [[Bravo Otto]] is a German accolade presented by the [[Bravo (magazine)|''Bravo'' magazine]].<ref>{{cite book|last=Blazek|first=Matthias|title=The Mamas and The Papas: Flower-Power-Ikonen, Psychedelika und sexuelle Revolution|date=December 2014|publisher=ibidem-Verlag, ibidem Press|language=German|isbn=978-3-8382-6577-3|page=17}}</ref> \n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|2013\n|rowspan=\"3\"|Little Mix\n|Newcomer of the Year \n|{{Won|place=Gold}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bravo.de/sport/bravo-otto-wahl-part-3-waehle-die-bffs-und-das-hot-couple-262953.html|title=BRAVO Otto-Wahl&nbsp;\u2013 Part 3: W\u00e4hle die BFFs und das Hot Couple|work=Bravo|accessdate=September 18, 2018|date=January 15, 2014|language=German|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160920161813/http://www.bravo.de/sport/bravo-otto-wahl-part-3-waehle-die-bffs-und-das-hot-couple-262953.html|archivedate=September 20, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|2018\n|rowspan=\"2\"|Best Band/Duo\n|{{Nominated}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=BRAVO-Otto-Wahl 2018: Vote f\u00fcr deinen Star! |url=https://www.bravo.de/bravo-otto-wahl-2018-vote-fuer-deinen-star-379763.html |website=Bravo |accessdate=24 October 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181024213844/https://www.bravo.de/bravo-otto-wahl-2018-vote-fuer-deinen-star-379763.html |archivedate=24 October 2018 |language=German}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=\"row\"|2019\n|{{Won|place=Gold}}\n| style=\"text-align:center;\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=BRAVO-Otto-Wahl 2019: Vote f\u00fcr deinen Star! |url=https://www.bravo.de/bravo-otto-wahl-2019-vote-fuer-deinen-star-382841.html |website=[[Bravo (magazine)|Bravo]]|accessdate=23 October 2019 |language=German}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Brit Awards==\nFirst awarded in 1977, the [[Brit Awards]] are the highest profile music awards ceremony in the UK recognizing popular music and sponsored by [[MasterCard]].<ref>{{cite web|title=BRITs Duo On Track To Reach Dizzee-ing Heights in UK Charts, 19 February 2010|url=http://bpi.co.uk/press-area/news-amp3b-press-release/article/brits-duo-on-track-to-reach-dizzee-ing-heights-in-uk-charts.aspx|publisher=[[British Phonographic Industry]]|accessdate=16 June 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100922212152/http://bpi.co.uk/press-area/news-amp3b-press-release/article/brits-duo-on-track-to-reach-dizzee-ing-heights-in-uk-charts.aspx|archivedate=22 September 2010}}</ref> Little Mix has received two awards from nine nominations.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"| 2016 \n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\"| \"[[Black Magic (Little Mix song)|Black Magic]]\"\n| British Single of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"b\">{{cite web|url=http://www.capitalfm.com/brits/news/2016-nominations/#DIXpCPQSyVQizc7C.97|title=BRIT Awards 2016 Nominations|work = CapitalFM |publisher=CapitalFM|date=14 January 2016|accessdate=14 January 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n| British Video of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"| 2017\n|-\n| Little Mix\n| British Group\n| {{nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"3\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/7697649/brit-awards-2017-winners-list|title=Brit Awards 2017: See the Full Winners List|work = Billboard|date=22 February 2017|accessdate=1 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n|-\n|\"[[Shout Out to My Ex]]\"\n| British Single of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|\"[[Hair (Little Mix song)|Hair]]\" <small>(featuring [[Sean Paul]])</small>\n| British Video of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"2\" |\"[[Touch (Little Mix song)|Touch]]\"\n|British Single of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |last1=Hedges-Stocks |first1=Zach |title=The Complete Guide to the Brit Awards 2018 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/news/complete-guide-brit-awards-2018/ |website=The Telegraph |accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|British Video of the Year\n| {{nominated}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |last1=Hedges-Stocks |first1=Zach |title=The Complete Guide to the Brit Awards 2018 |url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/music/news/complete-guide-brit-awards-2018/ |website=The Telegraph |accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| 2019\n|Little Mix\n|British Group\n| {{nom}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=Nominees for the Brit Awards 2019 |url=https://www.brits.co.uk/nominees# |website=Brit Awards |accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|\"[[Woman Like Me (Little Mix song)|Woman Like Me]]\"<small> (featuring [[Nicki Minaj]])</small>\n|British Video of the Year\n| {{won}}\n|<ref>{{cite web |title=British Artist Video of the Year Nominees Announced |url=https://www.brits.co.uk/news/british-artist-video-of-the-year-nominees-announced |website=Brit Awards |accessdate=12 January 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==British LGBT Awards==\nThe [[British LGBT Awards]] are a British award show that aim to recognize individuals and organizations that display \"outstanding\" commitment to the LGBT community. LGBT celebrities or straight allies are among the people that are recognised. Little Mix have received one award from two nominations.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| 2019 \n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|Little Mix\n|Celebrity Ally\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=2019 Winners |url=https://www.britishlgbtawards.com/winners-2019/ |website=British LGBT Awards |accessdate=20 May 2019 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190520175152/https://www.britishlgbtawards.com/winners-2019/ |archivedate=20 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |last1=Newman |first1=Vicki |title=Who won at the British LGBT Awards 2019? All the winners including Little Mix |url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/3am/celebrity-news/who-won-british-lgbt-awards-16162469 |website=Mirror |accessdate=20 May 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=Rita Ora and Demi Lovato lead British LGBT Awards 2019 shortlist |url=https://www.standard.co.uk/showbiz/celebrity-news/rita-ora-and-demi-lovato-lead-british-lgbt-awards-2019-shortlist-a4058166.html |website=Evening Standard|accessdate=5 February 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|Change Makers\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==Beano Awards==\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2017  \n|rowspan=\"1\"|\"[[Power (Little Mix song)|Power]]\" <small> (featuring [[Stormzy]]) </small>\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Pop Song of the Year\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Cite web|title= Beano Awards 2017 votes|URL = https://www.beano.com/posts/pop-song-of-the-year-2017-vote-now-in-the-beano-awards?channel=beano-awards|work=Beano|access-date= 2017-02-20}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2019\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Little Mix\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Favourite Music Artist\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Cite web|title=Beano Power Awards - Meet the Winners!|URL=https://www.beano.com/posts/beano-power-awards-meet-the-winners|work=Beano|access-date=2020-02-08}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==BreakTudo Awards==\n{{main|BreakTudo Awards}}\n\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2016  \n|rowspan=\"2\"|Little Mix \n|rowspan=\"2\"|International Group  of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Cite web|title= BreakTudo Awards 2016 indicados|URL = http://www.breaktudo.com/confira-lista-de-indicados-do-breaktudo-awards-2016-anitta-maju-trindade-justin-bieber-e-selena-gomez-esta-entre-os-concorrentes/ |work=BreakTudo|access-date= 2016-10-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| [[2017 BreakTudo Awards|2017]]\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|  <ref>{{Cite web|title= A Fazenda: Marcos Harter, Emilly Ara\u00fajo e Vivian Amorim est\u00e3o concorrendo no BreakTudo Awards 2017|URL = http://oportaln10.com.br/fazenda-marcos-harter-emilly-araujo-e-vivian-amorim-estao-concorrendo-no-breaktudo-awards-2017-67544/|work= Portal N10|access-date= 2016-10-11}}</ref>\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\"| \"[[Power (Little Mix song)|Power]]\" <small>(featuring [[Stormzy]])</small>\n| Best Video\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| [[BreakTudo Awards 2018|2018]]\n|Mixers \n| Best Fandom\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |last1=Cruz |first1=Marco |title=BreakTudo Awards 2018 announces nominees including BTS, BLACKPINK, Cardi B, Taylor Swift, and more! |url=https://www.kpopc