n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2013\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Little Mix\n| Ultimate Export\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>[http://www.cosmopolitan.co.uk/celebs/ultimate-women-of-the-year/winners-list-2013 Cosmopolitan Ultimate Women Awards] Retrieved 12 December 2013</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2015\n| The Ultimate Girl Group\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>[http://www.cosmopolitan.com/uk/entertainment/news/a39993/ultimate-women-awards-2015-the-winners-list/ Cosmopolitan's Ultimate Women of the Year Awards 2015: full winners list] Retrieved 1 April 2017</ref>\n|}\n\n==European Diversity Awards==\nThe European Diversity Awards is an annual award created by Linda Riley, managing director of Square Peg Media in 2012, to honour individuals and organisations who work to help create a more inclusive society in Europe.<ref>{{cite web |last1=Riley |first1=Linda |title=How the European Diversity Awards were created |url=https://www.theguardian.com/careers/square-peg-media-european-diversity-awards |website=[[The Guardian]] |accessdate=11 November 2019 |date=21 May 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=EDA CELEBRATING THE BEST IN DIVERSITY ACROSS EUROPE |url=https://www.europeandiversityawards.com/ |website=European Diversity |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref>\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2019\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| Media Icon of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=EDA SHORTLIST 2019 |url=https://www.europeandiversityawards.com/shortlist-2019.html |website=European Diversity |accessdate=11 November 2019}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==Girls Choice Awards==\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2019  \n|rowspan=\"1\"|Little Mix\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Most Empowering Music Group of the Year\n| {{Nominated}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{Cite web|title=Girls\u2019 Choice Music Nominees Announced|URL=https://extratv.com/2019/11/27/girls-choice-music-nominees-announced/|website=ExtraTV|accessdate=29 November 2019}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Glamour Awards==\nThe [[Glamour Awards]] is hosted by [[Glamour (magazine)|Glamour]] magazine every year to hand out different awards to honor extraordinary and inspirational women from a variety of fields, including entertainment, business, [[sports]], [[music]], [[science]], medicine, education and [[politics]]. The awards started in 2003 and are hosted every May and June in the [[United Kingdom|U.K.]] Little Mix have been nominated for four awards and have won three.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2012\n| rowspan=\"4\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| Band of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://shows.stv.tv/downton-abbey/latest/307630-glamour-women-of-the-year-awards-2012-full-list-of-winners/|title=Glamour Women of the Year Awards 2012: full list of winners|publisher=stv||accessdate=2015-05-29}}</ref> \n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2014\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"All the winners and gossip from the GLAMOUR Awards\">{{cite web|author=Glamour'' Women of the Year Awards|title=All the winners and gossip from the GLAMOUR Awards|year=2014|url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/news/celebrity/2014/01/31/glamour-awards-winners-news-nominees|access-date=3 June 2014|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140802131419/http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/news/celebrity/2014/01/31/glamour-awards-winners-news-nominees|archive-date=2 August 2014|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2016\n| rowspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"| Music Act Of The Year\n\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"GLAMOUR Awards 2016: Vote now and win tickets to the night!\">{{cite web|author=Glamour'' Women of the Year Awards |title=GLAMOUR Awards 2016: Vote now and win tickets to the night! |year=2016 |url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/news/celebrity/2016/01/29/glamour-awards-2016-voting-form |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160225175137/http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/news/celebrity/2016/01/29/glamour-awards-2016-voting-form |archivedate=2016-02-25 }}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2017\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Glamour Women of the Year Awards: All the winners\">{{citeweb|author=Glamour'' Women of the Year Awards |title= Glamour Women of the Year Awards: All the winners |year= 2017 |url=http://www.glamourmagazine.co.uk/article/glamour-awards-2017}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Global Awards==\n{{main|Global Awards}}The [[Global Awards]] are held by Global and rewards music played on British radio stations. Little Mix has won five out of nine nominations, the most of any artist. \n\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"| 2018\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Group\n| {{won}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.capitalfm.com/news/global-awards-2017-vote-now|title=Global Awards Vote Open |work=globalawards.com|accessdate=20 December 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best British Artist or Group\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Pop\n| {{nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| \"Power\" <small>(featuring Stormzy)</small>\n| rowspan=\"2\"| Best Song\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"| 2019\n| rowspan=\"1\"| \"[[Woman Like Me]]\" <small>(featuring [[Nicki Minaj]])</small>\n| {{Won}}\n| rowspan=\"4\" align=\"center\"|<ref>{{cite web |title=The Global Awards Returns In 2019 |url=https://www.capitalxtra.com/global-awards/the-global-awards-2019/ |website=Capital FM |accessdate=19 December 2018 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20181219153814/https://www.capitalxtra.com/global-awards/the-global-awards-2019/ |archivedate=19 December 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Group\n| {{Won}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best British Artist or Group\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Pop\n| {{Nominated}}\n|-\n|