abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/03/16/11/yeng-dominates-myx-music-awards-2011|title=Yeng dominates myx music awards 2011|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131222030115/http://www.abs-cbnnews.com/entertainment/03/16/11/yeng-dominates-myx-music-awards-2011|archivedate=22 December 2013|date=16 March 2011|publisher=[[ABS-CBN News Channel]]|accessdate=21 June 2015}}</ref>\n\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2017\n| \"Shout Out To My Ex\"\n| rowspan=\"2\"| [[Myx Music Award for Favorite International Video|Favourite International Video]]\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://myxph.com/myxmusicawards/vote/ |title=Shout Out to My Ex |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170630092524/http://myxph.com/myxmusicawards/vote/ |archivedate=30 June 2017 |accessdate=20 June 2017 |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2018\n| \"Touch\"\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>https://www.rappler.com/entertainment/music/197103-myx-music-awards-2018-nominations</ref>\n|}\n\n== Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards ==\n[[The Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards]], also known as the KCAs or [[Kids Choice Awards]], is an annual awards show that airs on the Nickelodeon cable channel, which is usually held on a Saturday night in late March or early April, that honors the year's biggest television, movie, and music acts, as voted by Nickelodeon viewers. Little Mix had one nomination and one win.\n\n=== Nickelodeon Kids' Choice Awards ===\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2017\n| Little Mix\n| Favorite Global Music Star\n| {{Won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Favorite Global Music Star (2017)\">{{cite web|author=Little-MixUS|title=Little Mix nominated for a Kids Choice Award|year=2017|url=http://www.milenio.com/hey/musica/nominados-kids_choice_awards-2017-milenio-noticias_0_896310656.html/}}</ref>\n|}\n\n=== Meus Pr\u00eamios Nick ===\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2017\n| Little Mix\n| Favorite International Artist\n| {{Won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://capricho.abril.com.br/famosos/sairam-os-indicados-ao-meus-premios-nick-2017/ |title=Sa\u00edram os indicados ao Meus Pr\u00eamios Nick 2017 |publisher=Capricho|accessdate=September 6, 2017|date=September 5, 2017|language=Portuguese}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Popjustice's Twenty Quid Music Prize ==\nThe [[Popjustice \u00a320 Music Prize]], also known as the Popjustice Twenty Quid Prize, is an annual prize awarded by music website Popjustice to recognise the best British pop single of the previous year. The prize was conceived by Popjustice founder Peter Robinson in 2003 as a reaction to what he perceived as the pompous and elitist nature of the existing Mercury Prize, which recognises the best album of the previous year, and in particular its exclusion of pop music acts in favour of those from more esoteric genres. The shortlist for the Popjustice prize is announced in September of each year and the winner named the following month, to coincide with the presentation of the Mercury Prize. Popjustice gives a token prize of \u00a320 to the winner of its award, in contrast to the \u00a320,000 given to the winner of the Mercury Prize.\n\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2012\n| \"[[Wings (Little Mix song)|Wings]]\"\n|rowspan=\"6\"|Track of the Year\n| {{nom}}\n|rowspan=\"6\"|<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.popjustice.com/twentyquidmusicprize/ |title=The 2016 Popjustice Twenty Quid Music Prize |work=PopJustice |accessdate=1 April 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2013\n| \"[[DNA (Little Mix song)|DNA]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2014\n| \"[[Move (Little Mix song)|Move]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2015\n| \"[[Black Magic (song)|Black Magic]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2016\n| \"[[Love Me Like You]]\"\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2017\n| \"[[Touch (Little Mix song)|Touch]]\"\n| {{won}}\n|-\n|}\n\n== Radio Disney Music Awards ==\nThe [[Radio Disney Music Awards]] is an annual awards show by Radio Disney. The awards honor the year's biggest achievements in music, voted by teen viewers. Winners receive an authentic full size Golden Mickey Mouse designed with the graphics of that year's show. The ceremony is not televised beyond commercial interstitial segments for Disney Channel. Little Mix have received two nominations and one win.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2014\n| \"[[Wings (Little Mix song)|Wings]]\"\n| Best Song to Dance To\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Radio Disney Music Awards\">{{cite web|author=Radio Disney Music Awards|title=Best Song To Dance To|year=2014|url=http://blogs.disney.com/disney-playlist/2014/02/22/just-announced-the-2014-rdma-categories-and-nominees/}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2017\n| \"[[Shout Out to My Ex]]\"\n| Best Break-Up Song\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Radio Disney Music Awards 2017\">{{cite web|author=Radio Disney Music Awards|title=Best Break-Up Song|year=2017|url=http://musica.disneylatino.com/rdma/}}</ref>\n|}\n\n== Shorty Awards ==\nThe [[Shorty Awards]], also known as the Shorties, are an annual awards event that honors the best short-form content creators on the micro-blogging website Twitter and on other social media sites. The awards have primarily been sponsored by the John S. and James L. Knight Foundation, and are organized by the co-founders of the Brooklyn-based startup company Sawhorse Media.<ref>{{cite web |last1=KHOSLA |first1=PROMA |title=5 moments from the Shorty Awards that show the power of new media |url=https://mashable.com/2016/04/12/shorty-awards-2016/ |website=Mashable |accessdate=19 February 2020 |date=12 April 2016}}</ref> Since their creation in 2008, the awards have expanded beyond Twitter to recognize content creation on other social networking sites, including YouTube, Tumblr, Foursquare, and Facebook.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2014\n| rowspan=\"3\"| Little Mix\n| Best UK in Social Media\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Best UK in Social Media\">{{cite web|author=Shorty Awards|title=Best UK in Social Media|year=2014|url=http://shortyawards.com/category/6th/uk |accessdate=20 June 2017}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2015\n| Best Band\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Shorty Awards\">{{cite web|author=Hollywood Reporter|title=Shorty Awards 2015|year=2015|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/shorty-awards-2015-nominees-include-778517?|accessdate=2 March 2015}}</ref>\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2016\n| Best Musician\n| {{nom}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref name=\"Shorty Awards 2016 \">{{cite web|author= Shorty Awards |title=Shorty Awards 2016 list winners |year=2016|url=http://shortyawards.com/8th/winners|accessdate=8 August 2016}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==Silver Clef Award==\nThe [[Silver Clef Award]] is an annual UK music awards lunch which has been running since 1976.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n| align=\"center\"| 2017\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Little Mix\n| rowspan=\"1\"| Best Live Act\n| {{won}}\n| align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://blog.ticketmaster.co.uk/music/little-mix-voted-best-live-act-o2-silver-clefs-34114|title=Little Mix voted your Best Live Act at O2 Silver Clefs|work=Ticketmaster UK|accessdate=2017-06-30}}</ref>\n|-\n|}\n\n==SSE Live Awards==\nThe SSE Live Awards are an annual music award which are voted and decided by the public, honouring the best live acts of the year at SSE venues.\n{{awards table}}\n!{{Abbr|Ref.|Reference}}\n|-\n|rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| 2019  \n|rowspan=\"1\"|Little Mix\n|rowspan=\"1\"|Best Group\n| {{nom}}\n| rowspan=\"1\" align=\"center\"| <ref>{{cite web |title=SSE Live Awards 2019 Winners |url=https://ssereward.com/sseliveawards/ |website=SSE REWARD |accessdate=19 February 2020}}</r